phase-1 — QA & Testing Agent — status report

Scope deliverables
------------------
1. Stand up the test harness (unit, integration, e2e layers) and wire it into CI.
2. Write unit tests for authorization logic.
3. Write integration tests for the profiles module against a test database.
4. Write tests that verify the RLS policies — users cannot access others' data.

Harness layout
--------------
Vitest 2.1.9, node environment, scoped via `--dir` per layer.

  vitest.config.ts             - single config, three opt-in scopes
  tests/_helpers/env.ts        - TEST_SUPABASE_* env contract, self-skip logic
  tests/_helpers/supabase-clients.ts - admin / anon / asUser client factories
  tests/_helpers/test-users.ts - createTestUser, deleteTestUsers, companion fixture
  tests/_helpers/server-only-stub.ts - empty stub for the `server-only` marker

Scripts in package.json:
  npm run test               -> unit only (CI merge gate)
  npm run test:unit          -> unit only
  npm run test:integration   -> integration only (self-skips without env)
  npm run test:rls           -> RLS only (self-skips without env)
  npm run test:all           -> unit + integration + rls

CI gate
-------
.github/workflows/ci.yml runs `lint → type-check → test` on every PR + main
push. The unit gate is the merge gate; integration & RLS suites are
opt-in and self-skip on machines without TEST_SUPABASE_* configured.

