Integration tests — tests/integration/profiles.test.ts (17 tests, env-gated)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Runs against a real Supabase test project (TEST_SUPABASE_* env). Self-
skips on CI / local dev machines without the env. Covers the database
contract /api/profiles depends on:

  PUT /api/profiles/me        insert path; update path; rate_cents bounds;
                              service_radius_m bounds; cross-user insert
                              blocked by RLS companion_profiles_insert_self.
  GET /api/profiles/[id]      verified-only public visibility (rule #9);
                              owner-self even when unverified.
  availability windows        valid insert; CHECK availability_window_order
                              (end<=start rejected); FK to companion_profiles;
                              list ordered by (day_of_week, start_time);
                              ON DELETE CASCADE from companion_profiles.
  photo reference             owner can set + clear avatar_path.
  self-promotion guard        CHECK companion_profiles_verified_at_set
                              blocks bare `verification_status = 'verified'`.

RLS policy tests — tests/rls/policies.test.ts (16 tests, env-gated)
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Source of truth: supabase/migrations/20260515000600_rls.sql. Two unrelated
authenticated clients plus an anon client prove that user B cannot reach
user A's data except through allow-listed paths.

  users                       users_select_self (positive + negative);
                              anon read blocked;
                              users_update_self blocks cross-user update;
                              users_select_verified_companion grants
                              discoverability after verification (restored
                              after the test).
  companion_profiles          companion_profiles_select_self;
                              companion_profiles_select_verified hides
                              unverified rows;
                              companion_profiles_insert_self blocks
                              writing a profile for another user;
                              companion_profiles_update_self blocks cross-
                              user update;
                              no delete-for-others (no policy → no rows).
  availability                availability_select_self;
                              availability_select_public_verified hides
                              windows of unverified companions;
                              availability_insert_self / _update_self /
                              _delete_self all block cross-user writes.
  messages, payments,         anonymous reads blocked on all four;
  bookings, meal_requests     reviews remain publicly selectable per policy.

Booking-participant policies (messages_select_participant,
payments_select_participant, reviews_insert_completed_participant, etc.)
require fixtures that depend on a real bookings flow. The bookings module
has not yet landed; those tests will be added alongside it. Header-level
comment in tests/rls/policies.test.ts records the deferral.

